==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Macacus
<hw>Ma*ca"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., a word of
African origin. Cf. <er>Macaco</er>, <er>Macaque</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of monkeys, found in Asia and the East
Indies, now usually called <altname>Macaca</altname>. They have short
tails and prominent eyebrows. See also <er>Macaca</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>macadam</ent>⟦br⟧
